Safety at the country's beaches is in the spotlight. It follows a number of drownings this festive season. CAPE TOWN - Thousands of holidaymakers are flocking to the coast over the holiday period. But often the fun and festivities are marred by accidents and drownings. Safety at the country's beaches is in the spotlight. It follows several drownings this festive season. READ: Christmas Day drownings reported across SA The NSRI's Craig Lambinon said volunteers are busier than ever. The organisation appealed to holidaymakers to only swim at beaches protected by lifeguards. Parents and caregivers are also urged to ensure that children are supervised in and around the water and when swimming.